  "name": "Blood Vendetta",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "<p><strong>Requirements</strong> You can bleed.</p><p><strong>Trigger</strong> A creature deals piercing, slashing, or persistent bleed damage to you.</p><hr /><p>You curse the target, punishing it for having the audacity to spill your blood. The target takes 2d6 persistent bleed or spirit damage and must attempt a Will save.</p><hr /><p><strong>Critical Success</strong> The target is unaffected.</p><p><strong>Success</strong> The target takes half the persistent bleed or spirit damage.</p><p><strong>Failure</strong> The target takes the full persistent bleed or spirit damage. Until the the persistent damage stops, the target has weakness 1 to piercing and slashing damage. @UUID[Compendium.pf2e-misc.our-items.Item.kuKHEWqtnb8IUl4O]{Spell Effect: Blood Vendetta (Failure)}</p><p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> As failure, but the target takes double the persistent bleed damage.</p><hr /><p><strong>Heightened (+2)</strong> The persistent damage increases by 2d6.</p>"
    },
